introduction: The real bad rage starts in the middle of the video. This never gets old.

vocabulary.definition: moving in a quiet and secretive way to avoid being noticed
vocabulary.example: I caught him sneaking out of the house past curfew.

vocabulary.definition: making changes to the structure or form of something
vocabulary.example: They are remodeling their kitchen to have a more modern look.

vocabulary.definition: concerned with beauty or the appreciation of beauty
vocabulary.example: The artist's paintings have a unique aesthetic that captivates viewers.
He was filled with rage when he discovered his car had been stolen.
The lecture was so boring that many students fell asleep.

vocabulary.definition: a large crowd of people, especially one that is disorderly and intent on causing trouble or violence
vocabulary.example: The police had to disperse the unruly mob that gathered in the city center.
